  "learn": {
    "heading": "Area of a rectangle, then add",
    "intro": "<p>A <strong>net</strong> shows every face of a box laid flat. The <strong>area</strong> of each rectangular face is <strong>length × width</strong>. To get <strong>surface area</strong>, find each face's area and <strong>add them all together</strong>. The answer is in <strong>square units</strong>.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>One face:</strong> a 5 × 2 rectangle has area 5 × 2 = <strong>10</strong> square units.",
      "<strong>Add the faces:</strong> if three faces have areas 10, 10, and 6, the total so far is 10 + 10 + 6 = <strong>26</strong> square units."
    ]
  },
